The Chronicle Sukulwenkosi Dube-Matutu, Online Reporter A Filabusi man is on the run after he allegedly fatally stabbed his friend in a dispute over the sharing of gold proceeds. Matabeleland South provincial police spokesperson, Inspector Loveness Mangena confirmed the incident which occurred on 12 June in Mabuze Village. She said the accused, Newman Mafu accused Nkosana Dube of shortchanging him of the money they had realised after selling gold. “I can confirm that we recorded a murder incident which occurred in Filabusi area. On 12 June at around 2PM the now deceased Nkosana Dube (25) and accused Newman Mafu (23) were watching soccer at Mabuze Football Pitch when they had a misunderstanding. Mafu accused Dube of giving him a small share of the money they made through selling gold. Mafu threatened to kill Dube but they were refrained by other community members,” she said. Insp Mangena said on the same day, around 9PM, Dube was drinking beer with Mr Mehluli Nkala and other patrons. They went outside to relieve themselves and the accused followed them and stabbed Dube on the chest and also stabbed Mr Nkala on the back. Dube died on the spot while Mr Nkala was rushed to hospital. Insp Mangena said investigations were underway. “The accused person is still at large and we appeal to members of the public with information that could lead to his arrest to contact the police. We also urge members of the public to desist from engaging in violence when faced with disputes. People should engage third parties such as community leaders or find other amicable ways to resolve problems,” he said. @DubeMatutu